30:39.368 --> 30:43.705
- Is that all you've had to eat?
- I don't have an appetite.

30:43.739 --> 30:45.974
Not for dinner, anyway.

30:49.255 --> 30:52.691
Libby, I've had a long,
trying day.

30:52.725 --> 30:55.394
So unwind with your wife.

30:55.428 --> 30:56.695
Pretend you're 27 again.

30:56.729 --> 30:58.957
No, I think
I'll draw you a bath instead.

30:58.965 --> 31:01.033
Good idea...
we can get in together.

31:01.067 --> 31:02.634
No, no, no, no, no.

31:02.669 --> 31:05.604
The tub
won't accommodate us both.

31:05.638 --> 31:07.839
I'll put on some hot coffee.

31:52.285 --> 31:53.919
The cards won yesterday.

31:58.936 --> 32:00.759
Aren't you even going to ask?

32:02.261 --> 32:06.722
- About your guest? No. I'm not.
- And why is that?

32:07.035 --> 32:09.870
I trust you to tell me
what I need to know.

32:09.904 --> 32:12.007
"You trust me...?"

32:12.607 --> 32:18.412
Last night, your wife was upstairs in her
room, in your house, with another man.

32:20.749 --> 32:24.418
- That... that doesn't bother you?
- Of course it does.

32:24.452 --> 32:27.554
Well, then...
then act like it matters!

32:27.589 --> 32:31.391
- Act like I matter! Yell at me.
- I don't want to yell, Margaret.

32:31.426 --> 32:35.028
Because of what you've been up to?
Is that it? People in glass houses?

32:35.063 --> 32:36.692
I don't know
what you're talking about.

32:36.693 --> 32:39.651
I know
there have been other women.

32:40.743 --> 32:43.737
- No.
- I'm not blind. I... I...

32:43.772 --> 32:46.441
All your late nights,
the out-of-town conferences.

32:46.442 --> 32:49.070
I am the provost
of a major university.

32:49.077 --> 32:51.211
Yes,
you're a very important man

32:51.246 --> 32:55.582
who has not laid a hand
on his wife in six years.

32:55.617 --> 32:59.423
There are
no other women, Margaret.

33:01.703 --> 33:03.851
Then it's me.

33:04.494 --> 33:07.789
You don't want to fight for me

33:07.790 --> 33:10.330
because
you don't want me anymore.

33:10.963 --> 33:14.359
I can't imagine
my life without you.

33:15.136 --> 33:20.909
Everything I have,
everything that matters to me,

33:21.479 --> 33:23.343
I have because of you.

33:23.344 --> 33:25.912
But you don't want me,
do you, Barton?

33:25.913 --> 33:29.878
You don't want to...
Make love to me.

33:30.306 --> 33:34.836
- Why? What is wrong with me?
- Nothing.

33:35.177 --> 33:37.879
You are the most beautiful woman
in the world to me.

33:37.913 --> 33:40.808
Then why are we like this?

33:41.984 --> 33:44.285
Answer me.

33:49.858 --> 33:53.661
What is wrong with you?!
W-what is wrong with you?!

33:53.696 --> 33:56.331
Oh, God.

34:03.105 --> 34:05.239
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

34:05.274 --> 34:07.909
Good morning.

34:07.943 --> 34:09.744
Jane.

34:09.777 --> 34:11.746
Your new secretary.

34:11.780 --> 34:15.016
Dr. Masters, so nice
to be working with you again...

34:15.042 --> 34:17.810
This time, with my clothes on.

34:19.237 --> 34:21.103
Virginia, my office, please.

34:21.135 --> 34:24.679
Before you disappear, you have
six patients scheduled this morning.

34:24.679 --> 34:26.755
The first, Mrs. Holloway,
is at 9:30.

34:26.784 --> 34:28.585
You have a lunch
with a Dean Braverman.

34:28.620 --> 34:30.920
I wasn't sure if his name was
Dean or he is a dean,

34:30.956 --> 34:33.456
so I made a reservation at
the faculty club just in case.

34:33.492 --> 34:36.159
And, um, if you notice a smell
in your office,

34:36.194 --> 34:37.795
I had Jerry from maintenance

34:37.829 --> 34:41.831
attend to that coffee stain
on the carpet beside your desk.

34:42.003 --> 34:43.966
Thank you.

34:44.835 --> 34:48.773
There's one more thing
that Jane would like to tell you.

34:50.175 --> 34:51.876
"anesthesia."

34:51.909 --> 34:57.191
A-n-e-s-t-h-e-s-i-a.

34:57.328 --> 34:59.382
"Anesthesia."

35:14.432 --> 35:16.367
Good morning, sir.

35:24.810 --> 35:28.712
- Good night?
- What's that?

35:28.747 --> 35:31.081
Did you have a good night?

35:32.201 --> 35:33.528
Fine.

35:39.157 --> 35:41.659
You have a great day, sir.

35:45.463 --> 35:47.364
Hi.

35:49.000 --> 35:51.101
Libby.

35:53.038 --> 35:56.807
- Bill has a lunch.
- I assumed. Um...

35:56.842 --> 36:00.010
I'm actually here for my follow-up
appointment with Ethan.

36:00.381 --> 36:04.184
And I thought I would pop in
and see you.

36:05.650 --> 36:08.262
Um, you don't have an aspirin,
do you?

36:09.821 --> 36:13.562
It's a hospital.
We even have morphine if you want.

36:15.067 --> 36:17.535
Actually, um...

36:20.599 --> 36:24.076
There's something else that
I hoped you could help me with.

36:26.798 --> 36:30.174
Bill's been coming home late
recently...

36:30.208 --> 36:34.645
- A lot, often past 10:00.
- The study...

36:34.679 --> 36:37.014
The research has entered
a new phase.

36:37.048 --> 36:39.717
I-I know how important
the study is to him.

36:39.751 --> 36:40.885
I suppose to both of you.

36:40.919 --> 36:46.538
It's just, he's so tired
when he gets home, and...

36:48.159 --> 36:54.431
We haven't been finding time
for each other.

36:55.223 --> 36:57.759
Time
that a husband and wife need.

36:58.888 --> 37:00.556
You haven't?

37:01.006 --> 37:04.584
I just thought if you could get
him home before he's dead on his feet...

37:04.609 --> 37:08.292
I actually don't
handle Bill's schedule anymore.

37:08.293 --> 37:10.714
Right. It's Jane now.

37:13.829 --> 37:15.930
Should I be talking to her?

37:18.767 --> 37:22.503
No. No.
You don't have to say another word.

37:22.538 --> 37:24.806
I will find a way
to shift things around.

37:24.840 --> 37:27.008
Don't worry.

37:28.544 --> 37:31.179
This is absolutely
no concern of yours.

37:31.213 --> 37:33.755
She came to me.

37:34.883 --> 37:37.718
And you couldn't say, "I don't
feel comfortable discussing this"?

37:37.753 --> 37:41.055
She's my friend, Bill.
She was asking me for help.

37:41.089 --> 37:43.908
You know, Jonas Salk
volunteered himself and his family

37:43.926 --> 37:46.510
to be the first test subjects
for the polio vaccine.

37:46.541 --> 37:49.664
Werner Forssmann inserted
a urethral tube into his elbow,

37:49.698 --> 37:51.132
pushed it to his heart,

37:51.166 --> 37:55.790
then x-rayed himself to prove that
cardiac catheterization is possible.

37:56.205 --> 37:58.206
There is a long
and very healthy tradition

37:58.240 --> 38:02.278
of scientists making themselves
the subject of their own studies.

38:03.779 --> 38:06.347
Well,
I-I can't continue this work

38:06.381 --> 38:08.983
If it comes at the expense
of your marriage.

38:09.017 --> 38:12.086
I am not discussing
my sex life with you.

38:12.120 --> 38:14.864
According to Libby,
there's little to discuss.

38:16.849 --> 38:23.831
I am very clear on where the line is
between you and me and what we do here.

38:23.866 --> 38:26.715
- It is for the work.
- I don't need you to tell me that.

38:26.731 --> 38:30.534
So then whatever goes
on between us can't affect Libby.

38:33.475 --> 38:35.176
It won't.

38:35.210 --> 38:37.899
Just so we have
an understanding.

38:41.636 --> 38:46.944
So as soon as you and Libby
are back to normal,

38:47.334 --> 38:50.436
then you and I
can continue our work.

38:56.331 --> 38:57.431
Gini.

38:57.466 --> 39:00.701
Ethan,
what are you doing here so late?

39:00.736 --> 39:05.294
Delivering a linebacker
...11 pounds, 7 ounces.

39:05.295 --> 39:09.143
You could stick a helmet on this
kid and draft him right now.

39:09.177 --> 39:12.146
- Bill.
- Dr. Haas.

39:17.386 --> 39:21.022
Ethan, I've been
meaning to tell you the kids...

39:21.056 --> 39:22.857
They just love the car.

39:24.726 --> 39:27.762
Uh, well,
it's a good family car.

39:27.796 --> 39:30.091
I'm happy I could help.

39:34.736 --> 39:36.904
Bill?

39:41.877 --> 39:43.878
You home early?

39:51.186 --> 39:53.354
I'm locked out.

39:58.226 --> 39:59.603
Scared me to death.

39:59.604 --> 40:02.697
I saw your car in the driveway,
but I didn't know where you'd gone...

40:02.731 --> 40:05.800
I went to get some firewood
from the stack behind the garage.

40:05.834 --> 40:07.535
The door slammed shut.
I got locked out.

40:07.569 --> 40:10.972
- You're shivering.
- Because it's freezing.

40:13.241 --> 40:15.231
There.

40:16.411 --> 40:18.112
That's a nice look on you.

40:28.423 --> 40:30.992
I thought, uh,

40:31.026 --> 40:33.294
we could have dinner in front
of the fire tonight.

40:34.046 --> 40:37.732
You did? We haven't
done that in a long time.

40:37.766 --> 40:41.330
I'll go get dressed,
start dinner.

41:20.676 --> 41:22.310
I've missed you.

41:31.734 --> 41:34.488
Isn't the hotel on Sycamore?

41:34.523 --> 41:36.891
You mind if we get
something to eat first?

41:36.925 --> 41:40.428
No. No.

41:40.462 --> 41:43.130
Who do you think
he thinks I am?

41:44.433 --> 41:48.384
One of those golf pros at the club?
Maybe the handyman?

41:48.904 --> 41:53.378
I've never had any secrets from him.
But now I have you.

41:53.425 --> 41:58.345
And I want to keep you to myself
and at the same time, tell everyone.

41:58.380 --> 42:00.981
But you won't, right?

42:01.016 --> 42:03.117
I guess
what I'm saying is...

42:03.151 --> 42:06.828
There are these moments
when everything changes.

42:06.829 --> 42:10.658
Like the moment a nurse hands
you this little bundle

42:10.692 --> 42:14.762
and says, "Here is
your daughter, Mrs. Scully."

42:14.796 --> 42:19.502
Or your dad clutches your hand
as you walk down the aisle

42:19.503 --> 42:22.072
and you realize he's crying.

42:23.949 --> 42:30.678
Or the moment a very handsome young
doctor turns to you outside a theater

42:30.712 --> 42:33.881
and asks,
"Did you like the movie?"

42:33.915 --> 42:38.048
And suddenly
everything is different.

42:39.986 --> 42:44.039
You have saved my life,
dr. Langham.

42:51.766 --> 42:56.270
I don't have a thing for older women.
I have a thing for women.

42:58.573 --> 43:01.001
Okay, so maybe
Margaret could be my mother.

43:01.002 --> 43:04.011
B-but Jane was this...
Adventuress.

43:04.012 --> 43:07.081
She was a girl I could have
sex with while people watched.

43:07.115 --> 43:11.952
Tracy before that... she was...
she was a sex kitten.

43:11.987 --> 43:17.224
Diane was...
Unapproachable ice queen.

43:17.259 --> 43:21.629
So all of the women
in your life have been a type.

43:21.663 --> 43:24.711
Have any of them
been a person to you?

43:24.821 --> 43:27.268
See,
another stupid shrink question.

43:27.302 --> 43:31.438
Listen, all I know is
I was driving with Margaret,

43:31.473 --> 43:33.207
I was feeling great.

43:34.235 --> 43:36.418
I was gonna eat
a plate of linguini,

43:36.419 --> 43:39.213
we were gonna go to the hotel,
hump our brains out.

43:39.247 --> 43:42.283
That's a fun evening.
Am I right?

43:42.317 --> 43:44.513
And what happened?

43:46.021 --> 43:49.990
You know the high striker
at the amusement park...

43:50.025 --> 43:54.840
That thing where you take
the mallet and try to ring the bell?

43:56.698 --> 43:59.767
What if you took a whack at that
thing and the bell suddenly said,

43:59.801 --> 44:05.039
"Oh, my God. Oh, my God,
thank you.

44:05.073 --> 44:10.248
That feels so amazing, and I've never
been this happy in my entire life."

44:12.379 --> 44:14.915
It's not so much fun then,
anymore, is it?

44:14.950 --> 44:18.519
So the bell you're trying
to ring becomes animate...

44:18.553 --> 44:21.123
Becomes a person.

44:22.090 --> 44:24.994
Isn't our time almost up?

44:32.071 --> 44:33.905
Smart of you.

44:33.939 --> 44:38.435
Of course no one would know me
on the pediatric ward.

44:38.436 --> 44:40.821
Yes, I'm full of tricks today...

44:40.822 --> 44:43.424
Sneaking you in here,

44:43.932 --> 44:46.534
stealing your husband's sperm
from the sperm bank.

44:46.544 --> 44:49.483
I know you're angry
with me, Ethan.

44:50.533 --> 44:52.734
But I will just say this.

44:55.057 --> 44:57.518
You're saving my life...

44:58.193 --> 44:59.727
And Bill's.

44:59.761 --> 45:04.372
And if there is any way
that I could ever repay you...

45:06.935 --> 45:08.769
Before we do the capping...

45:13.341 --> 45:15.876
Can you...

45:15.910 --> 45:20.781
Look in this catalogue and
pick out some new sheets for me?

45:20.815 --> 45:23.684
Sheets a girl would like,

45:24.313 --> 45:27.082
That would make her feel
at home.

45:27.168 --> 45:31.592
Of course.
I would be happy to.

45:36.398 --> 45:39.252
Honeyed linen.

45:39.801 --> 45:41.869
I think its bran.

45:41.903 --> 45:46.040
No, the, um,
the shade of my new bedding...

45:46.074 --> 45:49.109
- For the apartment.
- You bought new bedding?

45:49.144 --> 45:51.779
Now that I've got a pretty
girl spending the odd night,

45:51.813 --> 45:54.648
I figured
I better spruce the place up.

45:58.353 --> 46:01.358
You like me staying over
every now and then?

46:01.359 --> 46:03.127
I do.

46:05.360 --> 46:08.429
My last girlfriend, she didn't
like spending the night.

46:08.463 --> 46:11.332
She has two kids... that's what
David was talking about.

46:11.366 --> 46:13.657
He got confused.

46:13.665 --> 46:16.370
Why are you telling me this?

46:16.404 --> 46:19.873
You said you wanted to snoop.

46:19.908 --> 46:23.028
Well, this is what you'll find.

46:23.522 --> 46:25.956
I had my heart broken.

46:28.183 --> 46:30.617
Is it over between you two?

46:33.221 --> 46:34.521
It is.

46:36.691 --> 46:39.745
I thought that we could
still be friends but...

46:39.862 --> 46:41.662
That's the past.

46:41.696 --> 46:45.766
You, me, honeyed linen, huh?

46:45.800 --> 46:48.802
That's the future.

46:48.837 --> 46:53.784
You, Vivian Scully...
you're my future.

47:02.050 --> 47:04.978
Are you actually late,
dr. Masters?

47:04.979 --> 47:07.525
When are we bringing in
the next batch of study subjects?

47:07.562 --> 47:09.997
I have four couples
for tomorrow night...

47:10.037 --> 47:12.038
- The Prescotts included.
- Good.

47:12.072 --> 47:14.073
Then if you're free
this evening,

47:14.108 --> 47:16.976
you and I can resume
our participation in the work.

47:17.011 --> 47:19.145
The matter
you were concerned about...

47:19.179 --> 47:20.580
It's been rectified.

47:20.614 --> 47:22.115
I'm so glad.

47:22.149 --> 47:23.516
And Libby...

47:23.550 --> 47:26.185
Is looking forward
to having her husband back.

47:26.220 --> 47:29.222
And that is the last
you will hear of it.

47:29.256 --> 47:30.857
You were right.

47:30.891 --> 47:34.914
There are lines we shouldn't cross.
This is one of them.

47:36.030 --> 47:38.836
This, uh...

47:40.426 --> 47:42.928
This is complicated for me.

47:46.140 --> 47:47.340
I mean...

47:50.044 --> 47:52.557
I love my wife.

47:53.213 --> 47:55.214
Okay.

47:55.249 --> 47:57.717
So what happened
the other night...

47:57.751 --> 48:00.169
I can't keep doing that.

48:00.654 --> 48:05.458
That's why, from now on,
it has to be a hotel...

48:05.492 --> 48:09.662
Someplace safe
where we have a routine...

48:09.697 --> 48:11.631
A protocol.

48:19.473 --> 48:22.709
Stitches are still in.

48:22.743 --> 48:25.478
I'll be careful.

48:25.512 --> 48:29.482
I realize
you could have left me there.

48:29.516 --> 48:31.384
Left you? Come on.

48:31.418 --> 48:35.214
You were under
no obligation to care for me.

48:37.458 --> 48:39.559
You could have gotten hurt.

48:39.593 --> 48:43.129
I got jumped last year.

48:43.163 --> 48:47.133
I wished to hell
someone had shown up to help me.

48:50.504 --> 48:52.904
I know.

48:53.734 --> 48:55.735
It's scary.

49:11.291 --> 49:13.844
I'm sorry.

49:14.828 --> 49:19.742
Jane is just so diligent, I couldn't
get her to leave for the day.

49:20.567 --> 49:23.970
She felt there were too many
hand notations in your wheeldex,

49:24.004 --> 49:26.405
so she stayed
to retype the entire thing.

49:26.440 --> 49:29.008
I was thinking
tonight...

49:29.042 --> 49:33.630
Female superior, both sitting,
partially reclined.

49:33.653 --> 49:36.883
The angle might be optimal
for clitoral stimulation.

49:36.917 --> 49:39.140
<i>The rocking horse.</i>

49:40.387 --> 49:42.188
I looked it up.

49:47.361 --> 49:49.996
She has been doing a good job,
though, don't you think?

49:50.030 --> 49:53.248
Who, Jane?
She's adequate.

49:53.249 --> 49:56.102
She's lasted two full days.

49:56.136 --> 49:59.088
That's two more days
than her predecessors.

50:00.174 --> 50:03.523
And be honest.
Hasn't she met all your needs?

50:12.386 --> 50:16.889
Last week, I got a thank-you
note from Chancellor Fitzhugh's wife.

50:16.924 --> 50:21.594
Apparently, I sent zinnias
for her 60th birthday.

50:21.628 --> 50:26.178
I don't think I could pick
Stella Fitzhugh out of a police lineup.

50:28.268 --> 50:32.014
- Plateau.
- Plateau

50:32.372 --> 50:35.141
Or a zinnia, for that matter.

50:35.175 --> 50:37.376
But you can.

50:37.411 --> 50:39.350
And did.

50:44.318 --> 50:48.621
Her name is Estelle,
for the record.

50:48.655 --> 50:52.933
And it's important
to keep the Chancellor happy.

50:57.497 --> 50:59.389
Should I slow down?

50:59.561 --> 51:02.335
Jane will make a fine secretary.

51:02.369 --> 51:06.873
But to really anticipate
someone's needs...

51:06.907 --> 51:09.792
That's a rare thing.

51:15.089 --> 51:18.150
- Eight.
- Nine. Wait.

51:18.185 --> 51:19.886
What?

51:19.920 --> 51:22.054
Catch up.

51:43.343 --> 51:44.710
Orgasm.

52:16.276 --> 52:19.445
We should eat if we're
going to go over the data.

52:19.479 --> 52:22.581
I could pick up some deli
from around the corner,

52:23.165 --> 52:25.066
or we could go out for a bite.

52:25.067 --> 52:28.203
I can't.
I have plans.

52:30.190 --> 52:31.958
At this hour?

52:31.992 --> 52:37.502
I'm meeting Libby
for a late dinner.

52:42.269 --> 52:44.930
Well, you're taking
her someplace nice, I hope.

52:44.931 --> 52:46.865
I am.

52:47.541 --> 52:49.556
We can review the data
in the morning.

52:49.557 --> 52:53.202
All right, then.
In the morning.

